        "content": "<p><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:#191813\">@Compendium[compendiums-mix-dnd5e.um5-rules.T77zvGdp7mn1uopU]{UM5 Ch.6: Exo-Armor Rules &amp; Descriptions}</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:#191813\">UM5 p.85</span></p>\n<p><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:#191813\">Hit Points &amp; Threshold</strong><span style=\"color:#191813\">: Exo-armor has its own hit point total, which the wearer can shunt damage to instead of taking it herself. It also possesses a threshold, which is the maximum amount of damage the suit can absorb (or shunt to its own hit points) from a single hit (the wearer taking the rest). If exo-armor is reduced to 0 hit points, it can no longer absorb damage, but is still functional.Â </span></p>"
